President Donald Trump spoke live with two American astronauts, Christina Koch and Jessica Meir, who were conducting the first all-women spacewalk outside the International Space Station. Trump congratulated the astronauts on their historic achievement and asked them to share a message with young women interested in space. The President also discussed plans for future space exploration, including a mission to the Moon and eventually Mars. He highlighted the importance of defending space and the progress being made in commercializing space activities. Trump also touched on other topics, including the situation in Syria and his recent visit to Texas.